  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-11-01",
    "date": "2007-11-30T16:57:50Z",
    "text": "Mortgage Disclosure Enhancement Act of 2007 - Amends the Truth In Lending Act to require additional mortgage loan disclosures by a creditor to a consumer, including: (1) ) the percentage of the loan, as compared to the appraised value of the property; (2) the term of the loan; (3) the monthly income of the borrower, as relied upon in making the loan; (4) the annual percentage rate of interest for loans that are fixed, and for loans that are variable; (5) prepayment fees; and (6) balloon payments.\n\nAmends the Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act of 1974 to conform with this Act."
  },
